enterprise and for military as well for the 
academic campus? No, I think on the contrary. A

22:23.011 --> 22:30.722
consultation done by scientists is really one of 
the ways to keep in touch with the real world. And

22:31.803 --> 22:39.774
scientists otherwise tend very easily to become 
too theoretical or irresponsible. If you are

22:40.716 --> 22:49.027
allowed to build airplanes that never have to fly, 
then it's possible that the design is not so

22:40.716 --> 22:49.027
crucially thought about. If the airplane has to 
fly, then other pressures on you to really solve

22:52.812 --> 22:58.538
problems in a realistic fashion. Correct me if I'm 
summing this up incorrectly. It's an awful

