these efforts, perhaps, he did not have time or so 
much understanding for the importance of

25:25.922 --> 25:41.802
sophisticated scientific facilities. He had 
largely a Puritan instinct that science should be

25:42.884 --> 25:50.053
done in an inexpensive fashion, which is very 
commendable. But for many things in modern

25:50.843 --> 25:53.465
science, that's not so easy. Cyclotrons are hard 
to make out of old pipes and things like that.

26:01.933 --> 26:10.802
Professor Nirenberg, Director Nirenberg, for 
example, has done a tremendous job in two fields

26:01.933 --> 26:10.802
particularly that I can see, probably more. But 
